.TH "ipv6_renew_options" 9 "ipv6_renew_options" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipv6_renew_options \- replace a specific ext hdr with a new one.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ipv6_txoptions *" ipv6_renew_options
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "struct ipv6_txoptions *opt "  ","
.BI "int newtype "  ","
.BI "struct ipv6_opt_hdr *newopt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
sock from which to allocate memory
.IP "opt" 12
original options
.IP "newtype" 12
option type to replace in \fIopt\fP
.IP "newopt" 12
new option of type \fInewtype\fP to replace (user-mem)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a new set of options which is a copy of \fIopt\fP with the
option type \fInewtype\fP replaced with \fInewopt\fP.

\fIopt\fP may be NULL, in which case a new set of options is returned
containing just \fInewopt\fP.

\fInewopt\fP may be NULL, in which case the specified option type is
not copied into the new set of options.

The new set of options is allocated from the socket option memory
buffer of \fIsk\fP.
